4: Heh, it was no match for us.
9:
Yeah, there's no mistaking it... It looks
exactly like the monster we ran into
on Paradise Isle when we were
helping Luca...
12:
It had to have come here from
another world—
26: Who invited you to the party?!
28: Bow before us... or crumble to ash!
32: Why dost thou tarry? Hunt thy prey!
41:
Where is thy courage, mortal? Thou
art now rearguard to an Ancient.
54:
Nothing inside, just like always. I
managed to snatch a Curse Crystal
though.
57:
...Well, if Vagner's here, I guess this
has got something to do with you
dragons.
64:
I detected the presence of a Serpent
and followed it, only to discover that
inferior imitation.
66:
I shall share no more information
than that.
83:
There's no mistaking it—the Star
Augurs are your enemy this time.
87:
You remember your previous
encounters with them, yes? Adala,
the woman who helped the pirate
Zegra, and Procheon, the one who
wreaked havoc on Palpebra.
89:
They possess the ability to traverse
worlds. They're also the organization
that I've been chasing down this
whole time.
93:
...In addition, they're most likely
involved with the Dracohazard
incidents that have been going on.
97:
Dragons and Star Augurs... I wonder
what Rooma has to do with them.
101:
It's quite difficult to obtain any
information about the Star Augurs,
in part because of their
world-traveling capabilities.
103:
But they're also skilled at masking
their presence through scapegoats.
They use people and organizations
already established in an area,
before quietly slipping away.
107:
...I'm willing to bet that Rooma can
lead us right to them.
113:
We will refrain from subjecting him
to excessive interrogations. In return,
you will be responsible for him. I
assume you'll find this agreeable?
121:
Your lovely town is filled with all sorts
of capable people. I'm sure you'll get
to the bottom of this sooner rather
than later.
126:
Sorry to keep you waiting! We found
more!
145: Couette? Stella? Am I... still dreaming?
148:
No, you're awake now! But that
doesn't mean that dream wasn't
real too!
164:
Well, he certainly seems to be
friendly.
168:
...Indeed. We can breathe a sigh of
relief for the time being.
172:
Um... Rooma, what about this
painting?
180:
You're amazing! It looks just like I
described!
184:
I'm just glad it turned out okay, since
I'm not used to drawing from
descriptions...
189:
You said there were a lot of these,
right? Leave the rest to me!
193:
Is this... magic? Magic's so cool,
Couette!
201:
Ah... I'm sorry. It looks very close, but I
think it's supposed to be more...
smooth?
206: Smooth... Do you mean like Dia?
216: Okay... I'll try depicting it again.
222:
We can try as many times as we
need to! This is nothing for us!
232:
What an impressive display. Not
even a king would have such means
available to him.
235:
So... You said that you came out of
one of these cylinders.
237:
The person who released you was a
woman named Capella, and she
was being hunted down the last
time you saw her.
240:
...She was probably a scientist. I
wonder if she had a falling out with
the rest of her organization...
244:
...I want to meet Capella. But I don't
want to cause more trouble—
250: It's okay. We'll take you to her.
255:
We shall do what we can to help. If
she aided your escape, she might
prove to be an ally.
259:
As you can see, we have our own
reasons to join in, so don't hold back
on our account.
268: Finished! If you wouldn't mind, Prika.
278:
Yeah, this is exactly it... I was inside
one of these...
282:
How very interesting. That is an
object from Qualia City.
285:
Specifically, it is a mutant
incubation chamber sold by an
affiliate of Noxel. We should be able
to track them down with this.
289:
Qualia City, huh? You think it's time
to finally bust out the thing?
293: You want to reveal it already?
296: I'm not a fan of holding out.
301: Uh, what are you two scheming?
305:
Hehehe, you'll just have to wait and
see!
